"title": "1335: blessing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1335",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Spiritual and material benefits given by God to be enjoyed. Blessing the name of God is also the appropriate response of believers to all that God has done for them.</p>\n<h2>God is the source of all blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:11-1Chr29:12\">1CH 29:11–29:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:11\">PSA 89:11</a></p>\n<h3>At creation he blessed humans with fertility and authority over the earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28-Gen1:30\">GEN 1:28–1:30</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The disobedience of Adam and Eve caused God to remove his blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:16–3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5-Gen6:7\">GEN 6:5–6:7</a></p>\n<h3>After the flood God renewed his promise of blessing to Noah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:1-Gen9:3\">GEN 9:1–9:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:22\">GEN 8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:10\">JOB 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:9-Ps65:13\">PSA 65:9–65:13</a></p>\n<h2>The blessings promised to Abraham</h2>\n<h3>The blessings included descendants and nationhood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:2-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:2–12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1-Gen17:8\">GEN 17:1–17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:18\">GEN 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:4\">GEN 26:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:11\">GEN 35:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:6-Exod1:7\">EXO 1:6–1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:10-Deut1:11\">DEU 1:10–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:13\">DEU 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:8\">1KI 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:23\">NEH 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:2\">ISA 51:2</a></p>\n<h3>The blessings included land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:8\">GEN 17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:7\">GEN 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:3\">GEN 26:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:8\">DEU 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:40\">DEU 4:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:8-Deut11:12\">DEU 11:8–11:12</a></p>\n<h2>The promises of blessing to Abraham were fulfilled in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:16\">GAL 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:25-Acts3:26\">ACT 3:25–3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a></p>\n<h2>Blessings promised to Israel</h2>\n<h3>Blessings of fruitfulness and prosperity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:13-Deut7:14\">DEU 7:13–7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:25\">GEN 49:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:10\">LEV 26:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:4\">DEU 15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:8\">DEU 28:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:12\">DEU 28:12</a></p>\n<h3>Blessings of good health and long life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:25-Exod23:26\">EXO 23:25–23:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:26\">EXO 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:15\">DEU 7:15</a></p>\n<h3>Blessings of peace and victory over enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:7\">DEU 28:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:22\">EXO 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:6-Lev26:8\">LEV 26:6–26:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:24\">DEU 7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:11\">PSA 29:11</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of being blessed by future restoration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:23\">JER 31:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:9\">ISA 61:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:17-Isa65:25\">ISA 65:17–65:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:25-Ezek34:31\">EZK 34:25–34:31</a></p>\n<h2>The conditions of God's blessings</h2>\n<h3>Fear of the Lord brings blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:40\">JER 32:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:1-Deut6:3\">DEU 6:1–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12-Deut10:20\">DEU 10:12–10:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:13\">ECC 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:10\">ISA 50:10</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience to the Lord brings blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:26-Deut11:28\">DEU 11:26–11:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:1-Deut28:14\">DEU 28:1–28:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:15-Deut30:20\">DEU 30:15–30:20</a></p>\n<h2>To bless God is to worship and adore him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:5\">NEH 9:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:26\">GEN 9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:20\">GEN 14:20</a></p>\n<h2>People may bless one another in the name of the Lord</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:24-Num6:26\">NUM 6:24–6:26</a></strong> <em>There is a close link between blessing and prayer.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:27-Gen27:29\">GEN 27:27–27:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:1-Gen49:28\">GEN 49:1–49:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:8-Ruth1:9\">RUT 1:8–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:20\">1SA 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:10\">1CH 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:39\">MAT 23:39</a></p>",
